main event: Two unidentified lights were sighted in Yakutat, Alaska on July 26, 1953, one blue and one green/yellow.
interesting points: The blue light was moving from zenith towards the south at an altitude of 20,000 feet,The green/yellow light moved from west to southeast at an altitude of 12,000 feet,Observation was made by FAA personnel at the airport,The objects were described as having no tails or trails,The sighting was evaluated and possibly concluded to be a meteor.
sighted object: two unidentified lights in the sky
witness description: FAA personnel and civilians with excellent reliability
